Date: Wed, 09 Apr 1997 23:21:31 -0400
From: "Robert A. LaBudde" <ral@lcfltd.com>
Subject: Re: PRO/AH> Salmonella infections - Australia (Victoria) (04)
It should not be overlooked that a common mode of transmission of salmonella
to food animals occurs by rodents (mice, etc.). In particular, this is
believed to be the source of S. typhimurium in poultry. Pigs enjoy a tasty
rat when they come across one, and this is believed to be the source of
trichina in hogs.
Consequently the effects of weather in Victoria may be apropos, not because
of effects on microbiota or stress, but simply due to the effects on the
indigenous rodent population.
---
